Since it is important that the times are equalin both updates, they should be constants. 
Also,there is no reason to delay the first one with 5 seconds. 
I think the second updates should also have onErrorResume, but I am not sure if it matters.

  private Flux<AppConfig> periodicRefreshConfiguration(EnvProperties environment) {
        final Duration initialDelay = Duration.ZERO;
        final Duration refreshPeriod = Duration.ofMinutes(1);

        final CbsRequest getConfigRequest = CbsRequests.getConfiguration(RequestDiagnosticContext.create());
        Flux<JsonObject> serviceCfg = createCbsClient(environment)
                .flatMapMany(cbsClient -> cbsClient.updates(getConfigRequest, initialDelay, refreshPeriod))
                .onErrorResume(throwable -> onErrorResume(throwable, Mono.just(new JsonObject())));

        final CbsRequest getDmaapConfigRequest = CbsRequests.getByKey(RequestDiagnosticContext.create(), "dmaap");
        Flux<JsonObject> dmaapCfg = createCbsClient(environment)
                .flatMapMany(cbsClient -> cbsClient.updates(getDmaapConfigRequest, initialDelay, refreshPeriod))
                .onErrorResume(throwable -> onErrorResume(throwable, Mono.just(new JsonObject())));

        return serviceCfg.zipWith(dmaapCfg, this::parseCloudConfig) //
                .onErrorResume(AppConfig::onErrorResume);
    }
